data.content:
**No Thread.Abort migration is needed here.**

Your code uses only `Thread.Start`, `Thread.Join`, and `Thread.Sleep` — none of which involve `Thread.Abort`, `ThreadAbortException`, `Thread.ResetAbort`, or `Thread.Interrupt`. These APIs work identically in modern .NET 8 and will compile and run correctly as-is.

---

**Optional modernization** (unrelated to Thread.Abort migration):

You could replace the manual thread management with `Parallel.ForEach` or `Task.Run` for cleaner code:

```csharp
public void RunBatch(List<WorkItem> items)
{
    Parallel.ForEach(items, item => Process(item));
}
```

Or with cancellation support (useful if you later need timeout/stop):

```csharp
public void RunBatch(List<WorkItem> items, CancellationToken token = default)
{
    Parallel.ForEach(items, new ParallelOptions { CancellationToken = token },
        item => Process(item));
}
```

These are **optional improvements** — your existing code requires zero changes to work on .NET 8.
